<TITLE> JCD protests 'death threats' against Farroque </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 13 (bdnews24.com)  Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal held demonstrations on Saturday protesting against reported death threats received by BNP chief whip Zainal Abdin Farroque. The BNP student wing held a protest rally outside the party's Naya Paltan headquarters and later brought out a procession. The leaders urged the government to stop torture on BNP leaders and activists. Farroque filed a general diary with Gulshan police on Friday night saying he received a series of death threats by phone through the day, after he called for a probe into corruption allegations against the prime minister's son in parliament on Thursday. The callers had reportedly told the senior BNP leader that he would be "taught a good lesson" for speaking against Sajeeb Wazed Joy, and threatened to kill Farroque and his family. b
